{
  "stem": "13690.1",
  "chunk_idx": 6,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was a new school that new benches, that I don't think so that even today is in existence.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Which I do remember distinctly, each individual student had his own bench, with high polish.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "This school-- all the furnitures from that school was, in the first week of the war, taking out and sent to Germany.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "So don't ever think that they did not know where it coming from.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They were plundering, confiscating.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 41,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "Whatever it was movable, they took it.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 42,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Not at all.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So this-- this is the next step, how they try to humiliate the people.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "In other words, by taking away the sustenance and to be able to support themselves, there were no humane ways.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Then, of course, people had to risk their lives and go out of the town, bringing in just staple food like potatoes, flour, just simply to be able to sustain and live.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Then, of course, came the ordinance of giving away personal possessions.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Like, for instance, jewelry.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "So, jewelry-- people were not so eager or fast to give, so they put this in hiding, and it was easy to hide jewelry.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 43,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "Nobody's going to be that stupid to give away diamonds if they had diamonds, or gold if they had gold.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Then they starting to come out with an ordinance-- being that they were preparing for the war with Russia, they took away all the furs that the people had.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not the question of fur coats or fur lining-- anything that they had.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Even if a coat had a fur collar, you had to strip your collar and deliver the collar to the Germans.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was [?",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 44,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Sammelstelle-- ?] that means to say, it was a collecting place.",
      "word_count": 11
    }
  ],
